solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minOperations(int n) {
        int ops = 0;
        while (n != 0) {
            if ((n & 3) == 3) {
                n++;
                ops++;
            } else {
                n >>= Integer.numberOfTrailingZeros(n);
                n >>= 1;
                ops++;
            }
        }
        return ops;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The algorithm greedily clears the least-significant set bit. Whenever two consecutive 1s appear (n & 3 == 3), adding 1 merges them into a single 1 at the next higher bit, reducing future operations. Otherwise, a single subtraction clears the lowest set bit. This minimizes total steps and uses only bit operations.

